<subSubSection id="C36E5BFCE410FFC2FCC0F82E84D7F853" pageId="18" pageNumber="107" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BCB0877E410FFC2FCC0F82E84D7F853" blockId="18.[811,1456,1977,2027]" pageId="18" pageNumber="107">ETYMOLOGY. — The specific epithet refers to its stipules which have beautiful subcordate shape and neatly arranged network venation.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
